Forwarded from: Moscow Mayor Sergei Sobyanin
In the north-west of the capital, the Renovation Program includes 431 houses, where more than 86 thousand people live. For the construction of new buildings, 40 starting sites have already been selected. Now in SZAO:

• 18 houses are under construction;
• 10 buildings - in design;
• 16 new buildings - put into operation and handed over for occupancy.

New neighborhoods need a developed social infrastructure. In the Kurkino area, the construction of an educational building for 550 children is being completed, in Mitino - a kindergarten for 150 children. In Khoroshevo-Mnevniki, it is planned to build a school for 1,200 students and two kindergartens, each with 350 places. In the Pokrovskoye-Streshnevo area, construction of a kindergarten has begun 150 places and schools for 850 students. Another school - for 825 places - will be ready soon. There are also plans to build two educational complexes: for 650 and 800 students. In total, about 8 thousand people have already received apartments for renovation in the North-Western Administrative District.
